ice 30 or so hps until you get HoS/Kragg/Focus, etc in the shaman line.  The helm and bracer have neat affects for those who need 'em.  And the BP's heal is an added bonus.  The legs are probably your best pieces as they have more ac and more sta than thrug legs and the pricesless invis effect.  Most pieces of thurg quest armor will be better for you at any levels.  The effects on the Cobalt is what really makes them useful still. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=31658">Raun Stonecutter</a> <a href="http://www.swordoffate.com"><Sword of Fate></a>

